    "# 5. Advanced Drift Diagnostics (Linking Drift to Importance)\n",
    "\n",
    "We observed that the highest drift features (from Phase 1) were not necessarily the most important ones. This phase rigorously tests that hypothesis and looks for **Concept Drift** (Class-Conditional Drift).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Goals:**\n",
    "1.  **Correlation Analysis**: Is there a relationship between how much a feature drifts (KS Statistic) and how important it is (SHAP)?\n",
    "    *   *Ideal Scenario*: Important features have LOW drift.\n",
    "    *   *Danger Zone*: Important features have HIGH drift.\n",
    "2.  **Class-Conditional Drift**: Does the distribution of **Frauds** change from Day 1 to Day 2? This is the true definition of \"Concept Drift\" ($P(X|Y)$ changes).\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5.1 Drift vs. Importance Scatter Plot\n",
    "We calculate three types of drift for every feature:\n",
    "*   **Global**: Day 1 vs Day 2 (All data)\n",
    "*   **Normal ($Y=0$)**: Day 1 Normal vs Day 2 Normal\n",
    "*   **Fraud ($Y=1$)**: Day 1 Fraud vs Day 2 Fraud\n",
    "\n",
    "Then we plot these against Feature Importance."
   ]
